- Coordinate with the Hydraulics designer for the drainage needs associated withbridge decks and to determine the size of drain required.[[SRC_2]]- Bridge deck drainage shall be reviewed by the State Hydraulics Office. A copy shallbe provided to the State Hydraulics Office for their review as soon as the Preliminary Plan has been developed.
- The length and width of the structure, profile grade, superelevation diagram, and any other pertinent information (such as location of drains) shall be includedin the Preliminary Plan.[[SRC_4]]- Roadway and bridge deck profiles shall be adjusted as much as possible to avoid having bridge drains on the bridge.
- If bridge geometry is such that drains are required, the number of drains shouldbe minimized as much as possible while still providing a bridge deck drainage design that meets required standards.[[SRC_6]]- Free draining backfill material shall be used below the expected high-water elevation.
- The number of weep holes shall be increased beyond that required for a standarddesign.[[SRC_7]]

