- The minimum size for all diamond-shaped warning signs facing traffic on a multi-laneconventional road where the posted speed limit is higher than 35 mph shall be 36 x36 inches.
- Except as provided in Paragraph 5 of this Section, the minimum size for all diamond-shaped warning signs facing traffic on a multi-lane conventional road where the postedspeed limit is higher than 35 mph shall be 36 x 36 inches.
- The minimum size for supplemental warning plaques that are not included in Table 2C-1 shall be as shown in Table 2C-2.
- If a diamond-shaped warning sign is placed on the left-hand side of a multi-lane roadway to supplement the installation of the same warning sign on the right-handside of the roadway, the minimum size identified in the Single Lane column in Table 2C-1 may be used.
- Signs and plaques larger than those shown in Tables 2C-1 and 2C-2 may be used (see Section 2A.11).
- The minimum size for all diamond-shaped warning signs facing traffic on exit and entrance ramps at major interchanges connecting an Expressway or Freeway with an Expressway or Freeway should be the size identified in Table 2C-1 for the mainline roadway classification (Expressway or Freeway). If a minimum size is not provided in the Freeway column, the Expressway size should be used. If a minimum size is not provided inthe Expressway column, the Single Lane size should be used.[[SRC_1]]- Except as provided in Section 2A.07, the sizes for warning signs shall be as shown in Table 2C-1.
- The minimum size for all diamond-shaped warning signs facing traffic on a multi-laneconventional road where the posted speed limit is higher than 35 mph shall be 36 x36 inches.[[SRC_2]]- Except as provided in Paragraph 2 of this Section or unless specifically designated otherwise, all warning signs shall be diamond-shaped (square with one diagonal vertical) with a black legend and border on a yellow background.[[SRC_3]]- Type 1—a diamond-shaped sign, at least 18 inches on a side, consisting of either a yellow (OM1-1) or black (OM1-2) sign with nine yellow retroreflective devices,each with a minimum diameter of 3 inches, mounted symmetrically on the sign, or an all-yellow retroreflective sign (OM1-3).[[SRC_4]]- The minimum sign and plaque sizes for signs specific to bicycle-only facilities and shared-use paths shall be those shown in Table 9A-1. These sizes shall be used only for signs and plaques installed specifically for bicyclist applications.
- Any diamond-shaped warning sign that is placed such that it is applicable only to bicyclists or pedestrians on shared-use paths or separated bicycle lanes may be18” x 18”.[[SRC_5]]- Type 1—a diamond-shaped sign, at least 18 inches on a side, consisting of either a yellow (OM1-1) or black (OM1-2) sign with nine yellow retroreflective devices,each with a minimum diameter of 3 inches, mounted symmetrically on the sign, or an all-yellow retroreflective sign (OM1-3).[[SRC_6]]

