PROMPT 83: What are ADA requirements for curb ramp flare slope and width?
======================================================================
RESPONSE:
- Where provided, curb ramp flares shall not be steeper than 1:10.
- The landing clear length shall be 36 inches (915 mm) minimum. The landing clearwidth shall be at least as wide as the curb ramp, excluding flared sides, leading tothe landing.
- Curb ramps and the flared sides of curb ramps shall be located so that they do notproject into vehicular traffic lanes, parking spaces, or parking access aisles. Curb ramps at marked crossings shall be wholly contained within the markings, excluding any flared sides.[[SRC_1]]- The maximum slope of the flare shall be 1:10 (see Fig. 12(a)). Curb ramps withreturned curbs may be used where pedestrians would not normally walk across the ramp (see Fig. 12(b)).[[SRC_3]]- The running slope of the curb ramp run shall be parallel to the curb and shallbe 1:12 (8.3%) maximum, Exception: Where the curb ramp run length must exceed 15feet (4.6 m) to achieve a 1:12 (8.3%) running slope, the curb ramp run length shall extend at least 15 feet (4.6 m) and may have a running slope greater than 1:12 (8.3%).
- The cross slope of the curb ramp run shall be 1:48 (2.1%) maximum.[[SRC_5]]- Slopes of curb ramps shall comply with 4.8.2. The slope shall be measured as shown in Fig. 11. Transitions from ramps to walks, gutters, or streets shall be flushand free of abrupt changes. Maximum slopes of adjoining gutters, road surface immediately adjacent to the curb ramp, or accessible route shall not exceed 1:20.[[SRC_6]]

